Save state engine, Pocket-carried deltas:

1. Report a rejected load up to the Pocket loader. When the header magic check
   fails, raise ss_load_reject (sticky until the next load arms) so
   save_state_controller can fail the load at once instead of waiting out its
   ~10 s trigger timeout.

2. Force an NMI when a save/load request has stayed armed too long without a
   vector fetch. Some sections (title screens polling input) run with NMI
   disabled and no IRQ, so the engine never gets a hijack point. After 2^20
   MCLK (~48.8 ms) ss_nmi_force ORs one NMI into the 65C816. Ported from
   SNES_MiSTer PR #488.

3. CX4 coprocessor save state support: cx4_regs_sel/cx4_cache_sel decode, the
   $63 register and $8A cache windows, and holding the snapshot/restore until
   the CX4 is idle (cx4_ss_ok). Ported from SNES_MiSTer PR #487.

diff --git a/rtl/upstream/savestates.sv b/rtl/upstream/savestates.sv
index 8e567ec..1df632a 100644
